<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6899] SolrJ CollectionAdminRequest classes should not support public setters for action</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6899</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There shouldn&apos;t be public action setters for the CollectionAdminRequests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To elaborate more, a Create object should be able to do just that, doesn&apos;t make sense to support/have the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Create c = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Create();
c.setAction(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;RELOAD&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The implementation could have an action = &amp;lt;custom action&amp;gt; in case of custom actions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
